Setting the Axes Center Coordinate for Panning

This example shows how to set the axes center coordinate in space to achieve a panning effect.
A = imread("roses-se.jpg");
imshow(A)
axis on
What is the current center location?
center = getAxesCenterXY
center = 12
500.5000 500.5000
Now move the location to the center. This will have the effect of shifting the image up and to the left.
setAxesCenterXY([750 750])
Next, shift the image down and to the right by moving the location to the center.
setAxesCenterXY([250 250])
